		"description": "<p>You are permanently&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">blind</span> and can&rsquo;t see beyond the range of your blindsight. You can&rsquo;t benefit from any ability or magical effect that would grant you visual sight or darkvision. Your inability to see, however, is not without its advantages. You are immune to any illusion spell that relies on vision, such as blur<em>&nbsp;</em>, darkness, or invisibility<em>&nbsp;</em>, and you are also immune to attacks and effects that require meeting a creature&rsquo;s eyes, such as a&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">medusa&rsquo;s</span>&nbsp;petrifying gaze. Additionally, you gain an&nbsp;<span class=\"freelinking-link\">expertise die</span> on Perception checks that don&rsquo;t rely on sight.</p>",
